name: Bobby's Shack

reviews.review_text:
While the view is nice, beach facing and pretty scenes, the rudeness of the service staff is applaudable. We were served extremely cold soup and when we pointed it out, he made a dirty face and said "it is so hot". Also after taking our order of breads after 30 minutes he returns saying we don't have that particular bread.

The food is also average at best. The xacuti didn't feel unique at all and lacked flavour overall.

Avoid.

Dis shack is located at candolim beach in goa its 45 mins drive from mapusa taxi stand one of the pleasant and less crowded beach of goa if u ask abt ambience than its really cool and beautiful not very noisy and staff is very friendly and co operative one more thing they dont serve pork or beef so we selected this place for dinner ..we ordered chicken white cheese pasta it was the best white sauce pasta i had in time full of chicken and cream with olives but little oily so i asled dem to prepare it in less oil and to the point it was yummiest if u r white pasta sauce lover than this place is for u i ordered chicken steak it was ok ok in taste not great was sweet in taste i asked them to prepare little spicy so on request they did but not great yes i requested to put more vegetables and they acknowledged that was really good gesture of staff i really loved the place u can try on ur trip to goa they wont disappoint u little expensive

We have been coming to Goa for 15 years and always used Bobby's shack.  The food is excellent the staff are ALL attentive and very friendly.   Definitely the best shack in Goa.  You must visit this shack. Well done Sanjay Kash and all the hard working staff that have continued to maintain an excellent reputation in memory of dear Bobby godbless
Jack and Bridgette

description:
## Bobby's Shack: A Beachside Gem in Candolim

Nestled along the serene coastline of Candolim, **Bobby's Shack** has garnered a commendable rating of **4.1** from **753 reviews**, making it a noteworthy destination for both locals and tourists alike. Frequent mentions of its **beachfront location** (69 mentions), charming **shack-style** dining (24 mentions), and a vibrant atmosphere filled with **music** (15 mentions) and a selection of **cold beers** (11 mentions) paint a vivid picture of what to expect.

### Ambiance & Design

As you approach Bobby's Shack, the first thing that strikes you is its casual yet inviting atmosphere. The shack-style layout allows for seamless integration with the beach environment, offering stunning views of the Arabian Sea, as illustrated by customer-provided photos showing the picturesque sunsets and inviting seating. The images capture the essence of laid-back beach life, complemented by soft music that enhances the experience without overwhelming conversation.

### Menu & Culinary Experience

The menu at Bobby’s Shack features a delightful selection of dishes that cater to various palates. Noteworthy items include a **chicken white cheese pasta** that has charmed many patrons with its rich flavors, though some have noted it to be a bit oily. For those seeking a lighter option, the **vegetarian dishes** should not be overlooked. However, the mixed reviews on the **Goan xacuti** indicate that while some dishes shine, others may fall short of expectations. The presentation, as evidenced in the photos, is vibrant and appetizing, making for an enjoyable dining experience, though it does lack some consistency in flavors, as noted by a few guests.

### Customer Experience & Service

Customer experiences at Bobby's Shack have been varied, with standout service often praised. Some feedback points to exceptionally friendly and cooperative staff, particularly in accommodating requests like reducing oil in dishes or increasing spiciness where appropriate. However, there are unfortunate mentions of lapses in service that detracted from the experience. For instance, one customer mentioned receiving **cold soup** and a dismissive reaction from the staff. This dichotomy in service quality suggests a need for continued staff training amidst the generally positive reception.

### Popularity & Reviews

The restaurant enjoys a loyal following, with returning customers endorsing it as a staple of their Goa visits. A particularly touching review from a long-time customer highlighted the restaurant's consistent quality over the years, attributing its esteemed reputation to the dedication of the staff, including a heartfelt nod to the late Bobby. This sentiment underlines the restaurant’s legacy, fostering a community of repeat visitors who come for both the food and the atmosphere.

### Utilizing Visual Content

The ambiance and culinary presentations at Bobby’s Shack shine through in customer-shared photographs. The vibrant colors of the dishes juxtaposed against the backdrop of the beach create an inviting setting that is hard to resist. Images showcasing the rustic charm of the shack and the stunning beach views serve as a compelling invitation to anyone contemplating a visit.

### Conclusion

Bobby's Shack in Candolim stands as a testament to the charm of beachside dining, blending delightful cuisine with an inviting atmosphere. While the restaurant has received its share of critiques, the overwhelming sense of camaraderie and community keeps patrons returning, eager to enjoy a meal with sand between their toes and the sun setting in the distance. For those seeking an authentic Goan experience, it’s certainly a spot to consider, albeit with a discerning eye toward specific dish selections.
